  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nFor operational purposes, we want to be able to have a snapshotting process where a node starts up, syncs up with the blockchain, shuts down, and snapshots the disk. This way when we need to start new nodes, we can pull from a recent snapshot.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v1.0.3-65dcdc3\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nRight now nodes keep running after they catch up with the chain, and we have to monitor the node via HTTP to determine when it is up to date.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nIdeally there would be a flag we could set to shutdown automatically when a node is up to date. Most ETH 1 clients offer flags to this effect.",
